
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `airscan-discover` baraye peyda kardane scanner-haye shabake (network) estefade mishavad ke az protocol-haye eSCL va WSD estefade mikonand. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta scanner-haye mojood ra dar shabakeye khod peyda konid va az anha dar barname-haye scan estefade konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `airscan-discover --verbose`  --> 🗣️ Namayesh dadan etela'at bishtar dar morede scanner-haye peyda shode.
    🔹 `airscan-discover --timeout=<modat>` --> ⏳ Ta'een kardane modat zamani baraye jostojoo (be soorat saniye). Agar modat ra ta'een nakonid, az modat zamani pishfarz estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `airscan-discover --jostojoo-ye-khass <address>` --> 🎯 Faghat donbale yek address IP khass begard.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ airscan-discover

    🔹 Scanner-haye mojood dar shabake ra peyda mikonad.

    $ airscan-discover --verbose

    🔹 Scanner-haye mojood ra ba etela'ate bishtar namayesh midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ airscan-discover --timeout=5

    🔹 Be modate 5 saniye dar shabake donbale scanner-ha migardad va nataayej ra namayesh midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `airscan-discover` command is used to find network scanners that use the eSCL and WSD protocols. This command helps you discover available scanners on your network and use them in scanning applications.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `airscan-discover --verbose`  --> 🗣️ Display more detailed information about the discovered scanners.
    🔹 `airscan-discover --timeout=<duration>` --> ⏳ Specify the timeout duration for the search (in seconds). If you don't specify a duration, the default timeout is used.
    🔹 `airscan-discover --address <address>` --> 🎯 Only search for a specific IP address.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ airscan-discover

    🔹 Discovers available scanners on the network.

    $ airscan-discover --verbose

    🔹 Displays available scanners with more detailed information.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ airscan-discover --timeout=5

    🔹 Searches the network for scanners for 5 seconds and displays the results.

